can anyone from HS or anyone who has done this answer this?

I’m using pretty generic macro names which -if conflicts can occur scare me.
example macros:
```{{hamburger()}}
{{logo()}}
{{search()}}
{{menu()}}```

I had some problems with managing macros re-declared in different places. To avoid that at the end I have only one file now where I place all the macros and I just call the macros file if it isn't loaded like:
{% if not macros %}
  {% import "path/to/file/macros.html" as macros %}
{% endif %}

and the call will be:
{{ macros.titleMacro() }}
